---
import Layout from '../layouts/TamilLitLayout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Medieval Tamil Literature – Imperial Cholas">
  <div class="tamil-lit-wrapper">
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="hero-content">
        <h1 class="hero-title"><span class="tamil-text">இடைக்கால இலக்கியம்</span> Medieval Literature</h1>
        <p class="hero-subtitle">The Imperial Chola Era (900 CE – 1300 CE)</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header">
          <h2>The Age of Epics and Commentaries</h2>
          <div class="section-line"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="prose">
          <p>Under the Imperial Cholas, Tamil literature reached a new pinnacle of structural complexity and courtly grandeur. This was the era of Kambar's Ramavataram, Sekkizhar's Periyapuranam, and Jayamkondar's Kalingattuparani.</p>
          <div class="callout-box">
            <p><strong>Historical Context:</strong> Literature in this period was deeply tied to the legitimacy of the Chola state. The Periyapuranam was commissioned by Kulothunga II explicitly to counter the influence of Jain epics like Civaka Cintamani, solidifying Saiva Siddhanta as the state religion.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
